            a          <premis:PreservationPolicy> , dct:Policy;
            dct:title  "Preservation Plan" .
    
    <https://aussda.at/en/faq-downloads/faq/>
            a          <ex:SustainabilityPolicy> , dct:Policy;
            dct:title  "AUSSDA is an archive for the long-term storage of research data and has therefore taken precautions to secure data for as long as possible - for the lifetime of the archive and beyond. The University of Vienna, as coordinator of AUSSDA, has committed itself in its RDM policy to maintaining the infrastructure for research data management and ensures a long-term perspective. Storage for at least 10 years, which is usually regarded as good scientific practice and required by funding bodies, is thus guaranteed. In addition, AUSSDA is a CoreTrustSeal-certified and thus trustworthy repository - a criterion that funding bodies explicitly recommend when selecting a repository (see, for example, the RDM and funding criteria of the FWF or Horizon Europe)." .
    
